(153, 3, '2013-11-27 07:23:37', '2013-11-27 07:23:37', 'Paying homage to the traditional owners of the land, this powerful, collaborative work expresses the interplay of Australian culture and creativity.\r\n\r\neness craft an illuminating 360 degree projection mapped onto a 150 cubic metre mound of rocks. Blurring the virtual with the physical surroundings, the audience is encouraged to participate in a hyper-real environment.\r\n\r\nReal-time 3D content visualisations created by eness, the award winning art and design practice based in Melbourne, respond to the dynamic ambient soundscape.\r\n\r\nTransforming ordinary spaces and places into meaningful interactive experiences.\r\n\r\nA White Night Melbourne Commission.', 'Midden', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'midden', '', '', '2013-11-27 07:27:40', '2013-11-27 07:27:40', '', 0, 'http://whitenight.dev/?post_type=event&#038;p=153', 0, 'event', '', 0),
(154, 3, '2013-11-22 02:36:53', '2013-11-22 02:36:53', '<i>Midden </i>has been commissioned by White Night Melbourne for Birrarung Marr. Real-time 3D content visualisations created by ENESS, an award winning art and design practice based in Melbourne, will respond to the dynamic ambient soundscape. An illuminating 360 degree projection will be mapped onto a 150 cubic metre mound of rocks. <i>Midden</i> pays homage to the traditional owners of the land.  This powerful, collaborative work expresses the interplay of Australian culture and creativity.', 'Midden', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '153-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 02:36:53', '2013-11-22 02:36:53', '', 153, 'http://whitenight.dev/153-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(155, 3, '2013-11-27 07:01:12', '2013-11-27 07:01:12', 'At twilight all dimension differs. The crepuscular hours often associated with rays of light, from the sky leads us to the nocturnal.<i> Crepuscular Beam</i> by lighting designer Paul Collison sends a beam of ever morphing light far into the night sky, a visual beacon that attracts and leads to the darkened hours. The audience will be able to engage with the work from afar as the beams reach for kilometres into the night sky and also, up close, experience the lights ever evolving accompanied by an emotive soundtrack by Russell Goldsmith.', 'Crepuscular Beam', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'crepuscular-beam', '', '', '2013-11-27 12:19:03', '2013-11-27 12:19:03', '', 0, 'http://whitenight.dev/?post_type=event&#038;p=155', 0, 'event', '', 0),
(156, 3, '2013-11-22 02:41:02', '2013-11-22 02:41:02', '<i>Crepuscular Beam</i> is a large collection of searchlights staged in the centre of Melbourne. These roving, penetrating light forces will sweep the city providing a visual beacon that highlight central hubs of activity throughout the darkened hours of the night. The audience will be able to engage with the work from afar as the beams reach for kilometres into the night sky and also, up close, experience the lights morphing accompanied by an emotive soundtrack.', 'Crepuscular Beam', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '155-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 02:41:02', '2013-11-22 02:41:02', '', 155, 'http://whitenight.dev/155-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(157, 3, '2013-11-22 02:45:34', '2013-11-22 02:45:34', 'Set to feature on the external walls of the National Gallery of Victoria, this White Night Melbourne commissioned projection work will celebrate Melbourne’s skin art. Paying homage to the ever-increasing popularity of tattoos both flaunted and hidden, the exploration and beauty of this art form has been embraced by our city. Images of tattooed Melburnians, up close and personal, will be revealed and transformed into digital projections.', 'Tattooed City', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 02:45:34', '2013-11-22 02:45:34', '', 107, 'http://whitenight.dev/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(158, 3, '2013-11-22 02:46:12', '2013-11-22 02:46:12', '<i>Tim Winton’s The Turning </i>is a unique cinema event created by award winning Melbourne based director-producer Robert Connolly. Eighteen directors from diverse artistic backgrounds each interpret one chapter of Tim Winton’s novel <i>The Turning</i>. Set in a small coastal community, stories link and overlap depicting important life changing moments for its central characters. As the book was inventively adapted for the screen, the film’s exhibition has also been reimagined in an extraordinary way. Each chapter will be staged in a different environment and location that relates to the core themes. With most sites kept a secret, audiences will discover an emotive screen trail engaging in a film experience like no other.', 'Tim Winton\'s The Turning', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '132-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 02:46:12', '2013-11-22 02:46:12', '', 132, 'http://whitenight.dev/132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
