(258, 3, '2013-11-27 11:51:57', '2013-11-27 11:51:57', 'Melbourne based artist Anthony Ziella projects a compilation of some of the most important speeches to be captured on film from the most influential people of the 20th century. Despite the fact that these public addresses were given up to a century ago in such significant and specific moments in our collective history, they are still strikingly relevant today. In spite of the tremendous hardship that many of these figures faced, their messages promote peace, cooperation and altruism.\r\n\r\nZiella’s works fall somewhere between neo-expressionism and pop art. He experiments with found objects, predominately films, documentaries and specialises in portraiture.', 'Well May We Say', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'well-may-we-say', '', '', '2013-11-27 12:02:53', '2013-11-27 12:02:53', '', 0, 'http://whitenight.dev/?post_type=event&#038;p=258', 0, 'event', '', 0) ;
